<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
A classroom floor is rectangular. Its length is <m>{12}</m> m and its width is <m>{5}</m> m. Find the area of the floor.
</p>

<p>
Area = <fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/> <m>\text {m}^2</m>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The area of a rectangle is found using the formula:
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = l \times w
</me>
</p>

<p>
Here,
</p>

<p>
<me>
l = {12}\text{ m}, \quad w = {5}\text{ m}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Substitute the given values into the formula.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = {12} \times {5}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Multiply.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = {60}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the area of the classroom floor is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
{{60}\text{ m}^2}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>60</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>